node.title: Investors say new WA bill won't prevent another Juukan Gorge scandal
node.description: Investors have teamed up with Indigenous leaders in Western Australia to push for changes a new bill designed to prevent the destruction of Aboriginal sacred sites.

node.title: Rockhole is a 'quiet, wonderful' and overcrowded community. Now the NT's COVID outbreak has hit
node.description: On the edge of Katherine, by the river, around 350 people in the Binjari and Rockhole communities are at the new epicentre of the NT’s shifting COVID threat. But even before coronavirus, old and overcrowded housing was putting them at risk.

node.title: High cost of building supplies for residential housing investigated
node.description: Minister of Commerce and Consumer Affairs David Clark says there have been long-standing concerns about whether there is enough competition in the sector.
